JRemoteShell compiling instructions

Requierments 
============ 
In order to compile JRemoteShell you will need JDK (Java(TM) 2 Platform
 Standard Edition Development Kit) and Apache Ant.

Compile instructions
====================
To compile JRemoteShell go in the directory containing the sources and
execute: 

    ant

Run instructions 
================
To start the application: 

    java -jar dist/JRemoteShell.jar &

To connect at your shell in Linux or Mac OS X:

    nc localhost 8100

In Windows you can use putty connecting at localhost port 8100 using a
raw connection.